# Build parameters — the single source of truth. Edit here.
# Move to Debian 14: change DEBIAN_SUITE, then `./build.sh clean`.

DEBIAN_SUITE=trixie                              # Debian codename (13=trixie)
DEBIAN_MIRROR=https://deb.debian.org/debian
ARCH=amd64

# Editions to build. Each is defined declaratively in editions/<name>.env
# (which stacks, app tiers, Kali settings, and GPU variants it produces).
EDITIONS="everything security gaming"

ARCHIVE_AREAS="main contrib non-free non-free-firmware"
# (ISO volume ID is derived in auto/config — GENOS_<edition>_<variant>,
# truncated/uppercased to satisfy ISO 9660 / Joliet label rules.)

# Squashfs compression. live-build defaults to xz, which is slow (~19 min on a
# desktop rootfs). zstd is several times faster for a small size cost. Lower
# SQUASHFS_LEVEL (1-6) = faster build/larger ISO; raise toward 19-22 for a
# smaller release ISO. Both are env-overridable: sudo SQUASHFS_LEVEL=3 ./build.sh
#
# FAST=1 is a shortcut for quick dev iteration: it drops the squashfs level to 3
# (mksquashfs ~1m instead of ~4m) at the cost of a bigger ISO. An explicit
# SQUASHFS_LEVEL always wins over FAST. Use the default (12) for release ISOs.
#
# NOTE: put overrides AFTER sudo (sudo FAST=1 ./build.sh). `FAST=1 sudo …` is
# silently stripped by sudo's default env_reset, so the knob would do nothing.
if [ "${FAST:-0}" = 1 ]; then SQUASHFS_LEVEL="${SQUASHFS_LEVEL:-3}"; fi
SQUASHFS_COMP="${SQUASHFS_COMP:-zstd}"
SQUASHFS_LEVEL="${SQUASHFS_LEVEL:-12}"

# Optional apt caching proxy (apt-cacher-ng). When set, downloaded .debs are
# reused across editions, rebuilds, and even `purge` — turning cold builds warm
# and letting an all-editions run download the shared base only once. apt still
# GPG-verifies every package, so plain-http through the cache is safe (and
# required for the proxy to actually cache — see extras/apt-cacher.sh).
#   host build:      sudo APT_PROXY=http://localhost:3142 ./build.sh
#   container build: run extras/apt-cacher.sh, then
#                    sudo APT_PROXY=http://localhost:3142 ./container-build.sh
#                    (auto-adds --network host; VAR after sudo — see NOTE above)
APT_PROXY="${APT_PROXY:-}"

# Kali archive signing key (pinned, hard-fail on mismatch — same discipline as
# the Mullvad/LibreWolf installers). Verify/update per:
#   https://www.kali.org/blog/new-kali-archive-signing-key/
KALI_KEYRING_URL=https://archive.kali.org/archive-keyring.gpg
KALI_KEY_FPR=827C8569F2518CC677FECA1AED65462EC8D5E4C5
